218.0	Vladimir_Nabokov	Vladimir Nabokov	Nabokov's Lolita (1955) is frequently cited as among his most important novels and is his most widely known, exhibiting the love of intricate word play and synesthetic detail that characterised all his works. The novel was ranked at No. 4 in the list of the Modern Library 100 Best Novels. Pale Fire (1962) was ranked at No. 53 on the same list. His memoir, Speak, Memory, was listed No. 8 on the Modern Library nonfiction list.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/34/Vladimir_Nabokov.jpg/220px-Vladimir_Nabokov.jpg
